We also found that the BM MSC secretome alone was not sufficient for long-lived ASC survival and exogenous APRIL and BM hypoxic conditions provided enhanced longevity (
,
). We refer to the BM MSC secretome, exogenous APRIL, and hypoxic conditions as the human cell-free

 in vitro

BM mimetic (iBMM). Previous systems supported human ASCs with co-cultures of supportive cells for a few days or from

 in vitro

generated ASCs (
,
,
). Our unique system maintains freshly isolated human ASCs

 ex vivo

for 8–12 weeks and beyond (
).
